entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: An operating system or platform focused on AI agents and technical updates like database connectivity and development environment simplification. It has a presence on Twitter/X and GitHub.

entities.name: Clank Tank v2
entities.description: A platform for pitching ideas that includes media support for MP4 and YouTube videos. It is a significant development focus for ElizaOS.

entities.name: AI Agents
entities.description: A key development area for ElizaOS, these agents are trained on ElizaOS data to propagate their vision and facilitate discussions. A 'council of AI agents' is planned for community questions.

entities.name: Twitter/X
entities.description: A social media platform for public communication and visibility. ElizaOS experienced a suspension of its account for approximately two months.

entities.name: Jin
entities.description: An individual involved in the development and strategy of ElizaOS, announcing plans for Clank Tank v2 and new AI agents. Emphasizes the vision-selling aspect of AI agents.

entities.name: WSL
entities.description: Windows Subsystem for Linux, a compatibility layer that allows developers to run Linux tools and environments directly on Windows.

entities.name: Postgres
entities.description: A powerful, open-source object-relational database system known for its reliability and feature robustness.

entities.name: adapter-supabase
entities.description: A plugin that was previously required for database connectivity with Supabase; it is no longer needed for newer Eliza versions.

entities.name: Zerebro
entities.description: A project that was clarified to be a test with a parody episode, featuring challenges with API credits and crashing. The founder is no longer involved.

entities.name: Jeffy
entities.description: The former founder of the Zerebro project, who is no longer involved and has launched a new token.

entities.name: GPT-5
entities.description: An iteration of OpenAI's Generative Pre-trained Transformer models, known for advanced natural language processing capabilities.

entities.name: Kanban board system
entities.description: A visual workflow management tool designed to help visualize work, limit work-in-progress, and maximize efficiency. Can be implemented using AI.

entities.name: SQLite
entities.description: A C-language library that implements a small, fast, self-contained, high-reliability, full-featured, SQL database engine. It is a complete system that does not require a separate server process.

entities.name: tmux
entities.description: A terminal multiplexer for Linux, enabling users to create, manage, and switch between multiple terminal sessions within a single window.

entities.name: Cursor IDE
entities.description: An AI-first code editor built on VS Code, designed for a seamless developer experience with integrated AI features.

entities.name: Remote Explorer extension
entities.description: An extension for code editors that facilitates remote development, allowing users to connect to and manage remote environments.

entities.name: WSL extension
entities.description: An extension specifically designed to integrate the Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL) with code editors, improving the development workflow.

entities.name: Supabase
entities.description: An open-source Firebase alternative that provides a suite of tools and services for building backend applications, including a PostgreSQL database.

entities.name: yikesawjeez
entities.description: A community member who shared experiences with GPT-5 and the implementation of an AI-powered Kanban board system.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A freeware, initially game-focused, VoIP application that allows voice, text, and image communication for communities. Used here for community discussions.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform and version control system for software development, used for hosting and collaborating on projects. ElizaOS has a repository here.
